          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Determination of the nuclear scattering amplitude",
                " of uranium-235 by neutron diffraction.-"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2TUKCNA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Tr-1 reactor in conjunction with a"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SPECC"
                ],
                "institute": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Crytal spectrometer.",
                " The reactor has a power of 1 mega-watt."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The neutrons originating from the reactor",
                " are scattered on the (111) plane of a copper crystal",
                " which serves as a monochromator. The wavelength is",
                " 1.0824 angstrom."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Several U samples are used with different",
                " enrichments. All samples were metallic bars",
                " showing the powder character. They are described",
                " in table 1 of the main reference",
                " --------------------------------------------------",
                " sample    enrichment   weight    diameter   height",
                "           (percent)    (gram)    (cm)       (cm)",
                " --------------------------------------------------",
                " natural     0.71       75.039    1.270      3.175",
                " U-2        10.         75.808    1.271      3.178",
                " U-1        40.         75.604    1.270      3.176",
                " U-4        80.         74.861    1.270      3.178",
                " --------------------------------------------------",
                ".The samples are at room temperature. They are",
                " metallic andin alpha-phase with a base-centered",
                " orthorombic crystal structure.",
                ".The sample were obtained from cbnm,geel (belgium)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DIFFR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The diffracted intensity is measured."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BF3"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Proportional counter, containing 96 percent",
                " enriched B-F(3). Its sensitive length is 48.26 cm",
